methods.getPrevChunk:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Returns a chunk of previous data corresponding to the keys from the given RowSequence.

*Overload 1*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.engine.table.ChunkSource.GetContext) - A context containing all mutable/state related data used in retrieving the Chunk. In
          particular, the Context may be used to provide a Chunk data pool
  :param rowSequence: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSequence) - An RowSequence representing the keys to be fetched
  :return: (io.deephaven.chunk.Chunk<? extends DefaultChunkSource.WithPrev.ATTR>) A chunk of data corresponding to the keys from the given RowSequence
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param context: io.deephaven.engine.table.ChunkSource.GetContext
  :param firstKey: long
  :param lastKey: long
  :return: io.deephaven.chunk.Chunk<? extends DefaultChunkSource.WithPrev.ATTR>
methods.getPrevSource: :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.ChunkSource<DefaultChunkSource.WithPrev.ATTR>) a chunk source which accesses the previous values.
